 "components": {
  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: automatic_top_up, balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer, beneficiary_not_allowed, cancel_transfer, card_payment_fee_charged, card_payment_not_recognised, declined_cash_withdrawal, exchange_rate, exchange_via_app, failed_transfer, get_disposable_virtual_card, get_physical_card, passcode_forgotten, pending_top_up, pending_transfer, receiving_money, reverted_card_payment?, top_up_by_cash_or_cheque, top_up_reverted, topping_up_by_card, transfer_fee_charged, transfer_into_account, transfer_timing, verify_my_identity, verify_source_of_funds.\n\nIMPORTANT: You must output the category label EXACTLY as it appears in the list above, including any punctuation marks such as question marks or underscores. For example, the category for reverted card payments is 'reverted_card_payment?' (with a question mark at the end), not 'reverted_card_payment'.\n\nCLASSIFICATION RULES AND DOMAIN-SPECIFIC GUIDANCE:\n\n1. When a customer describes that a previous payment has been returned or reversed to their account after they already received the item or service, this should be classified as 'reverted_card_payment?' (note the question mark).\n\n2. When a customer asks about viewing their transfer history or checking what they have transferred, this relates to checking their balance after a bank transfer and should be classified as 'balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer'.\n\n3. Questions about PIN delivery, PIN arrival, or receiving a PIN separately are related to getting a physical card and should be classified as 'get_physical_card', NOT 'passcode_forgotten'. The 'passcode_forgotten' category is only for when a user has forgotten their existing passcode.\n\n4. 'get_physical_card' covers all aspects of receiving a physical card including: ordering a card, card delivery status, PIN delivery, and card activation.\n\n5. 'passcode_forgotten' is specifically for situations where the user cannot remember their current PIN/passcode, not for questions about receiving a new PIN.\n\n6. 'transfer_timing' is about how long a transfer takes to complete, not about viewing transfer history.\n\nOutput only the category label, with no additional text or explanation."
 },
